So, in other words,

24:18.466 --> 24:32.624
The only reason to reject Jesus as God's promised Messiah is if the eyes of your heart are blind to God's words and to God's workings in this world.

24:33.885 --> 24:44.398
I would say that was Paul's closing argument in front of this jury of his peers, Jewish people, Jewish people who loved the Lord, loved the scripture.

24:45.520 --> 24:47.282
Paul had made a reasoned argument

24:48.130 --> 24:51.173
And this would be his closing statement.

24:52.675 --> 24:55.999
His hope in prayer would be that they would just fall on their knees.

24:57.040 --> 25:03.447
Fall on their knees as did the Philippian jailer just a few weeks earlier and say, what must I do to be saved?

25:04.007 --> 25:07.411
I understand now what God has done to save me.

25:07.811 --> 25:09.313
What must I do?

25:11.656 --> 25:13.297
But as it worked out, they didn't do that.

25:15.019 --> 25:17.522
Paul's words just rolled off their backs.

25:17.634 --> 25:18.275
Most of them.

25:20.217 --> 25:29.366
What this jury did, perhaps after taking a vote, is reported in thought provoking statement five, and here it is.

25:29.706 --> 25:30.847
They formed a mob.

25:31.928 --> 25:32.689
That's what they did.

25:33.089 --> 25:35.672
They formed a mob and started a riot.

25:38.034 --> 25:40.897
You get the impression they couldn't out reason, Paul.

25:43.200 --> 25:45.682
None of them said, the scripture doesn't say that,

25:46.306 --> 25:48.448
Isaiah's not somebody we trust.

25:49.710 --> 25:53.494
I don't care if you're reading what Isaiah, no, they trusted Isaiah.

25:55.376 --> 25:56.918
They trusted all the prophets.

25:57.759 --> 26:09.972
They trusted everything it said in what we call the Old Testament scriptures, and Paul had carefully walked them through it to where there was no way they could reason themselves out from under it.

26:13.316 --> 26:15.538
And so we say here, if you can't use reason,

26:16.290 --> 26:17.452
use brute force.

26:19.054 --> 26:19.715
That's what they did.

26:19.735 --> 26:23.361
That's frequently the way things turn out in this fallen world.

26:23.782 --> 26:40.608
Religious people, professing Christian people, American professing Christian people give into the allure of getting by force what they cannot get by persuasion.

26:42.831 --> 26:44.594
American Christian involvement

26:45.026 --> 26:58.887
in what has been called the cultural wars over the last 50 years or so, has traded some simple statements of God's word and demonstrations of God's never-ending love for mankind.

26:59.348 --> 27:01.371
Those are the things we should talk about.

27:01.651 --> 27:02.553
What has God said?

27:03.174 --> 27:04.175
What has God done?

27:04.556 --> 27:13.970
How has God shown his love and just state the truth, but American Christians to some degree have traded the power of those statements.

27:16.162 --> 27:24.351
for the kind of power that can come at the ballot box.

27:24.371 --> 27:31.659
Let our votes be the bullets with which we destroy the arguments of the enemy.

27:36.324 --> 27:42.071
And if ballots are the weapons of choice, then it really doesn't matter who cast them.

27:42.891 --> 27:45.234
As long as the Christian goal

27:45.794 --> 27:46.615
is achieved.

27:48.558 --> 27:58.091
Now you notice that Luke reports that these Jewish people, these children of Abraham who didn't buy Paul's biblically based conclusions, they went to the marketplace.

27:59.473 --> 28:11.510
They went to the marketplace and rounded up what Luke calls some bad characters to strengthen their hands and to do for them what they couldn't do by themselves.

28:12.030 --> 28:14.674
That is shut up, Paul,

28:14.818 --> 28:19.844
and Silas, and show them to be wrong.

28:21.606 --> 28:24.129
We'll just get rid of them.

28:24.149 --> 28:27.854
We'll just get rid of them.

28:27.874 --> 28:44.594
This time though, unlike in Philippi, Paul and Silas escaped harm and poor Jason, who had housed them in his own home, was dragged before the magistrates as some kind of sacrificial lamb.

28:45.826 --> 28:59.866
However, in contrast to what happened in Philippi, here in Thessalonica, Roman law and order prevailed, and Jason was not flagged, flogged, or put into prison.

29:00.947 --> 29:08.858
He was merely presented as a befriender of some dangerous men, and so he was fined, and he was released.

29:11.322 --> 29:14.226
Now, thought-provoking statement six,

29:14.658 --> 29:22.488
contains the charge against Paul and Silas to which Jason was considered an accessory.

29:23.029 --> 29:23.689
And here we go.

29:24.070 --> 29:26.593
Here's what the outraged Jews said to the town officials.

29:27.074 --> 29:37.567
Six, these men, Paul Silas, probably Timothy and Luke as well, these men have caused trouble all over the world.

29:38.508 --> 29:39.289
How did they know that?

29:40.471 --> 29:42.994
They might know what had happened up in Philippi,

29:43.394 --> 29:50.105
and the news might have gotten down there, but they're just expanding it out to say what a troublesome bunch these are.

29:50.465 --> 29:52.969
These men have caused trouble all over the world.

29:53.330 --> 29:56.335
The King James version of the Bible, how many of you were raised on that?

29:58.058 --> 30:00.101
Now let me ask you a serious question.

30:00.461 --> 30:01.563
See how courageous you are.

30:01.904 --> 30:04.167
How many of you have a King James version with you today?

30:07.934 --> 30:08.755
It's okay.

30:09.536 --> 30:10.738
It's okay.

30:11.042 --> 30:22.593
But here's what the King James Version translated that verse, a phrase that has stuck in the church's mind for ever since the King James Version came out in English.

30:22.993 --> 30:28.238
They said in the King James Version, here are the men who have turned the world, what?

30:29.119 --> 30:30.380
Upside down.

30:31.621 --> 30:37.607
That's a more dramatic statement, isn't it, than just saying they've caused trouble all over the world.

30:38.528 --> 30:40.850
Now they've turned this world upside down.

30:43.330 --> 30:50.440
We've incorporated that phrase as the subtitle for our entire series of messages here that we're going through the book of Acts.

30:50.881 --> 30:59.794
The title is The Acts of the Apostle and then the subtitle that we print every week is Turning the World Upside Down.

31:01.116 --> 31:10.930
Now the truth is, as we pointed out last week, the ways of the world and the ways of Christ's church are mutually exclusive.

31:12.674 --> 31:13.615
And indeed they are.

31:14.436 --> 31:19.082
They certainly were for the churches that the Apostle Paul was raising up in the Roman world.

31:19.903 --> 31:30.317
The church of Jesus Christ when it is being the true church of Jesus Christ is one of the most troublesome organizations in the world.

31:33.020 --> 31:34.843
I'm just going to let that sit on you for a while.

31:38.928 --> 31:40.530
Don't raise your hands on this one.

31:41.762 --> 31:48.671
But how many of you have been persuaded in the last couple of years that the last thing we Christians want to be in the world is troublesome?

31:50.874 --> 31:52.336
Churches shouldn't be troublesome.

31:53.198 --> 32:01.028
Churches ought to be joyful, happy places where everybody wants to come and everybody goes home feeling better whether or not they believe in Jesus or not.

32:02.270 --> 32:08.338
But churches certainly be troublesome places and Christians shouldn't bring trouble into this world.

32:09.826 --> 32:14.513
Well, here's some troublesome words that Jesus once said.

32:15.654 --> 32:21.503
Matthew chapter 10 verse 34, do not suppose that I have come to bring peace to the earth.

32:22.704 --> 32:26.169
I have come not to bring peace, but a sword.

32:26.230 --> 32:34.962
Those are some red letter words that we don't usually include in our red letter reading.

32:36.834 --> 33:00.270
See, the truth that comes with the Spirit of Christ, rips and tears like a two-edged sword through all the demonic programs and proclamations that have shaped and controlled the thinking of the people of this fallen world ever since the fall of mankind in the Garden of Eden.

33:01.733 --> 33:05.138
God's truth rips that stuff apart.

33:07.714 --> 33:20.173
churches that are admired and praised by the people of the world are most likely leaving a lot of Christ's truth out of their proclamations.

33:22.316 --> 33:36.818
In recent days, to the shame, really, of us Americans, in recent days a million member fellowship of Methodists in Africa has cut ties

33:37.122 --> 33:45.436
as it were with their American counterparts over the issue of gay clergy and gay marriage.

33:46.237 --> 33:49.563
The American Association says, we embrace it.

33:50.404 --> 33:56.174
The African believers say it's not biblical, and we're going to even have to break fellowship with you.

33:57.016 --> 34:00.882
After all these years, it was an American missionaries who took the gospel

34:01.026 --> 34:01.847
to that land.

34:02.127 --> 34:16.245
It's American missionaries who built and encouraged those churches, many times laid down their lives in service to a lost group of people who have come to faith, many of them.

34:17.127 --> 34:29.202
And here's a million of them that are part of a fellowship, a Christian fellowship who says, if it means cutting like a sword, our ties with our American affiliation.

34:30.530 --> 34:32.312
over a matter of biblical truth.

34:33.633 --> 34:35.935
That biblical truth is what's doing the cutting.

34:37.356 --> 34:37.977
It's not us.

34:40.119 --> 34:43.202
Christ's truth always cuts through man's garbage.

34:46.385 --> 34:55.153
Christ's truth always cuts through people's natural inclinations to just keep everything copacetic.

34:56.875 --> 35:00.498
You see, we would certainly say

35:01.538 --> 35:15.513
could say, along with the protesters in Thessalonica, just Christian truth has the potential to create trouble all over the world, all over the world.

35:16.995 --> 35:27.666
In our homes, in our companies, even in our gatherings that are supposedly and generally religious.

35:28.674 --> 35:34.422
and the United States of America is no longer the great exception to that fact.

35:35.864 --> 35:50.084
Many are the societal practices and the legal standards raised up in this secular land of ours in recent years that violate the clear teachings of Scripture.

35:51.325 --> 35:57.714
Christian truth openly expressed has the possibility and likely the probability

35:58.146 --> 36:01.651
of creating great trouble for people.

36:02.532 --> 36:05.957
Christian truth can cause people to feel guilty.

36:06.017 --> 36:11.705
Christian truth can cause people to feel judged.

36:13.387 --> 36:19.716
Christian truth can create backlash even when it is spoken in love.

36:21.699 --> 36:26.866
For many in our land today, the old line from the music man

36:27.458 --> 36:36.772
Those of you who know that great show, I think of Dick Van Dyke playing the key part in the TV version.

36:38.474 --> 36:44.644
The old line from Music Man tweaked just a little bit, carries a relevant story.

36:45.445 --> 36:49.110
And here's what the main character sings.

36:49.290 --> 36:50.552
You might remember this.

36:51.293 --> 36:52.095
I'm not going to sing it.

36:52.896 --> 36:53.657
We got trouble.

36:55.259 --> 36:57.042
We got trouble right here.

36:57.698 --> 36:58.679
in River City.

36:59.320 --> 37:09.555
We got trouble right here in River City, I could say, the good old USA, and it starts with tea, and it stands for truth.

37:11.398 --> 37:11.778
Truth.

37:13.440 --> 37:22.994
God's revealed truth is indeed a problem, a troublesome thing for many in this land of ours.

37:23.874 --> 37:38.883
This land once felt the only reason to invest in universal public education was so that all Americans could learn to read and to understand and of course obey the Bible.

37:40.226 --> 37:42.290
That's how our public school system began.

37:43.106 --> 37:44.929
Everybody needs to know how to read.

37:45.269 --> 37:46.832
How else can they read the Bible?

37:47.072 --> 37:48.735
How can they learn God's truth?

37:48.935 --> 37:50.758
How can they build their lives around it?

37:50.998 --> 37:57.068
How can our country stay moral and good and strong if the Bible and its truths pass away?

37:57.329 --> 37:59.332
We've got to teach everybody how to read.

37:59.372 --> 38:02.677
That's how our public school system started.

38:03.218 --> 38:04.760
That was the passion behind it.

38:10.429 --> 38:10.930
Trouble.

38:11.298 --> 38:17.665
caused by God's word was not something our founding fathers envisioned.

38:17.725 --> 38:26.995
They thought the more people who know the word of God, the more people who build their lives upon the word of God, the better and better the country will be.

38:28.697 --> 38:36.586
They could have never imagined that God's word would be causing trouble in this land.

38:37.907 --> 38:39.068
But that trouble has come.

38:40.029 --> 38:40.690
Has it not?

38:41.730 --> 38:49.477
Now our seventh thought provoking statement zeros right in upon the main issue of Paul's day, Jesus versus Caesar.

38:49.517 --> 38:53.361
Here's how the protesters put it in that statement.

38:53.461 --> 38:59.086
Number seven, the protesters said they are defying Caesar's decrees.

38:59.707 --> 39:04.372
They are saying that there is another king, one called Jesus.

39:06.213 --> 39:08.936
And we know Jesus is not another king.

39:08.956 --> 39:11.218
He is the king of kings.

39:11.938 --> 39:12.419
Amen.

39:14.281 --> 39:14.722
No one.

39:15.884 --> 39:22.753
No one should exercise more control over our minds and hearts and behavior than the Lord Jesus Christ.

39:23.154 --> 39:29.783
His teachings directly counter many of the teachings of this current world.

39:31.426 --> 39:40.178
There are surely those who would say his teachings and what his church proclaim, some of them at least,

39:41.698 --> 39:44.783
could ruin our company.

39:46.786 --> 39:52.635
They could devastate our country, these so-called teachings of Christ.

39:53.697 --> 39:57.643
They could surely divide our communities.

39:59.686 --> 40:00.427
Indeed, they could.

40:01.990 --> 40:03.332
In fact, they already are.

40:03.372 --> 40:04.133
Are they not?

40:06.337 --> 40:07.218
Christians.

40:07.650 --> 40:17.721
are once again being identified as those whose teachings would turn this fine world of ours upside down.

40:20.804 --> 40:22.246
And that leads to our final thought.

40:23.367 --> 40:26.611
Christ's church does not go looking for a fight.

40:28.112 --> 40:31.816
At the door this morning, we will not outfit you with boxing gloves.

40:33.879 --> 40:34.820
We are not fighters.

40:35.721 --> 40:37.042
We are proclaimers.

40:38.114 --> 40:50.914
And we are proclaiming things that nevertheless cause people distress, that call them to repent and to change and to get right with God.

40:51.214 --> 40:56.803
And if they choose not to do any of those things, they will resist what we are saying.

40:57.183 --> 41:00.328
And they might, yes, fight back.

41:03.173 --> 41:06.738
But Christ's church does not go looking for a fight.

41:07.458 --> 41:12.024
But everywhere they go, they speak fighting words.

41:13.205 --> 41:15.628
Words that people can take issue with.

41:16.069 --> 41:19.553
Words that unbelievers have always taken issue with.

41:19.934 --> 41:27.984
Words that the devil takes issue with and swears against every day that he will destroy those words.

41:29.326 --> 41:31.068
Hide them in a corner somewhere.

41:32.089 --> 41:35.634
Make difficult lives for anyone who believes them.

41:39.234 --> 41:47.425
You see, believers in one way or another, true believers, are always saying in so many different situations.

41:48.366 --> 41:54.314
You know, the Bible tells me, and then they follow on with some statement.

41:55.236 --> 41:57.158
It's not like, I'm telling you you can't.

41:58.220 --> 42:00.863
You're not going after people and say, man, are you messed up?

42:00.883 --> 42:02.045
You've got to change.

42:02.065 --> 42:05.970
No, but it's enough to say God's word that I believe in with all my heart.

42:06.946 --> 42:16.701
God's word that came from the creator of the universe and the one before whom every one of us will someday give account.

42:17.503 --> 42:21.048
God's word tells me and then share something of it.

42:22.531 --> 42:24.013
It's up to them what they do with it.

42:24.674 --> 42:29.021
It's up to them whether the Holy Spirit actually opens their minds and their hearts to receive it.

42:29.522 --> 42:34.770
But if we say it, we know we will be saying things

42:34.946 --> 42:45.602
that will be received by some and rejected strongly by others, and in this day and age might even get us into some kind of trouble.

42:48.587 --> 42:50.049
But can we do that for Christ's sake?

42:50.990 --> 43:04.050
Have not his people been put in trouble through all the centuries simply because they declared, and most of the time declared it with loving intentions, the truth of God.

43:05.890 --> 43:07.312
We need to be committed to it.

43:07.392 --> 43:09.015
I'm declaring it to you now.

43:10.097 --> 43:13.062
Maybe some of you are troubled by what I'm saying this morning.

43:15.005 --> 43:15.806
Love you anyway.

43:17.890 --> 43:21.095
If you want to talk about any of this, let's do that.

43:22.197 --> 43:23.419
Let's bow and prayer, shall we?

43:24.961 --> 43:32.754
Our Heavenly Father, we surely recognize things that I for sure

43:34.018 --> 43:54.426
long decades ago, never thought I would ever have to recognize, not in this Christian nation, not in this good land, not surrounded by the vast numbers of people who profess the very thing I profess, at least generally.

43:56.529 --> 44:00.274
And we read the scripture and we see that spokesman for you

44:01.026 --> 44:07.474
who spoke words that were challenging to their society, got in trouble a lot.

44:08.695 --> 44:10.037
Their lives were threatened.

44:11.819 --> 44:18.908
Their words were challenged and rejected.

44:20.910 --> 44:30.482
Father, in the Old Testament, the prophet says, Lord, we've held all, we've opened up our arms all day to a disobedient people.

44:32.290 --> 44:33.412
And Father, now we too.

44:33.472 --> 44:42.706
To some degree at least, we too, in this country, get the share in what the Church of Jesus Christ has always shared in.

44:42.766 --> 44:51.899
The trouble that comes when you speak for God in a godless world.

44:53.582 --> 45:01.714
And yet, Father, every one of us in this room somewhere along the line had somebody speak that message to us and we accepted it.

45:02.242 --> 45:03.303
We believed it.

45:03.704 --> 45:05.085
We've been nurtured by it.

45:05.426 --> 45:11.713
And now we look back some of us many years upon having tried to live it out in our own lives.

45:12.995 --> 45:20.303
And so far that we know every time we share some of your word, the person we share it to might well embrace it.

45:23.227 --> 45:29.234
And others might reject it and spit on it and perhaps spit on us as well.

45:32.194 --> 45:37.182
But Father, we do it as the saints of old have done.

45:37.243 --> 45:39.266
We do it for Jesus' sake.

45:40.428 --> 45:48.722
And because it's true, and because you are our God, and we live our lives under your direction.

45:49.663 --> 45:51.226
So bless us now, we pray.

45:52.047 --> 45:55.954
This day and through this week, for we ask it in Jesus' name.

45:57.122 --> 46:03.112
We hope this message has inspired you to live the Sun Life together with us.

46:03.793 --> 46:11.766
If you are near Apple Valley, California this weekend, we invite you to join us in person Sunday morning or through our live broadcast.

46:12.347 --> 46:16.914
All the details are on our website at sunlifecommunitychurch.com.

